---
layout: base
permalink: /about/index.html
title: About
description: "Hello, fellow wanderer. I’m Bryan and this is my blog, a place where I write short status updates about what’s going on in my life, post photos, and occasionally shout into the void."
---

{% set readingPosts = collections.posts | withAnyTagSlugs("books,now-reading") %}
{% set readingPost = readingPosts[0] %}

<article class="content content-page h-entry">
  <header class="post-header">
    <h1 class="section-title p-name">About</h1>
    <nav class="about-social" aria-label="Social links">
      <a class="about-social-link" href="/@bryan" aria-label="Mastodon">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-mastodon" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="https://bsky.app/profile/afterword.blog" aria-label="Bluesky">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-bluesky" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="{{ site.microblogUrl }}" aria-label="Micro.blog">
        <i class="fa-brands fa-microblog" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
      <a class="about-social-link" href="/contact/" aria-label="Contact by email">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section class="post-full-content">
    <div class="content-body e-content">
      <p>Hey, thanks for stopping by.</p>

      <p>I’m Bryan. Around here I mostly post short updates about life, photos from around the Pacific Northwest, and the occasional thought about cities, music, or whatever else happens to be on my mind.</p>

      <p>The name <em>Afterword</em> comes from the idea that life is the story and this blog is where a few reflections land afterward.</p>

      <h2>Work</h2>
      <p>I’m an urban planner by profession and have spent nearly two decades working in long range planning, community development, and campus planning.</p>
      <p>Because of that, I spend a lot of time thinking about how places shape people. Cities, parks, transit, landscape architecture, and the psychology of the built environment tend to occupy a lot of space in my brain.</p>
      <p>I also write about urbanism at <a href="https://lowvelocity.org">Low Velocity</a>.</p>

      <h2>Where I&apos;m from</h2>
      <p>I grew up in the Great Lakes region but have lived in the Pacific Northwest for nearly a decade now.</p>
      <p>I love the forests and landscapes here, though Midwest nostalgia still sneaks up on me sometimes. This occasionally leads to dangerous amounts of Zillow browsing.</p>

      <h2>Life</h2>
      <p>Outside of work I mostly enjoy making things.</p>
      <p>Writing, music, photography, gardening, cooking, learning bits of web development, and slowly improving our home are all things I spend time on.</p>
      <p>I also spend a lot of time outdoors with my young family, so you’ll find plenty of photos from those adventures scattered around the site.</p>

      <h2>Interests</h2>
      <p><em>(in no particular order)</em><br>
      urban design, transit maps, photography walks, cedar forests after rain, guitar gear, Telecasters, tube amps, building guitars, live music, old concerts, sci-fi movies, gardening, tomatoes and peppers, cooking experiments, home projects, wandering cities, neighborhood walks, the Pacific Northwest, Midwest nostalgia, Italian genealogy rabbit holes, Italian bureaucracy, small personal websites, RSS feeds, maps, strange corners of the internet</p>

      <h2>A few random things</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>I built my own Telecaster.</li>
        <li>I have a terrible memory for movie titles and actors.</li>
        <li>I became an Italian citizen in 2020 after a long adventure through Italian bureaucracy.</li>
        <li>I keep a running list of concerts I’ve attended.</li>
        <li>My wife and I occasionally daydream about spending part of the year in Italy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <p>You can reach me by <a href="/contact/">email</a>, follow my <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a>, find me on <a href="/@bryan">Mastodon</a> or <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/afterword.blog">Bluesky</a>, read my urbanism writing at <a href="https://lowvelocity.org">Low Velocity</a>, or browse my <a href="/live-music-journal/">live music journal</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {% if readingPost %}
  <section class="section-block">
    <h2 class="section-title">Reading</h2>
    <div class="home-stream">
      {% set post = readingPost %}
      {% set streamImage = post | firstImage %}
      <article class="home-stream-item home-stream-item-reading h-entry">
        <p class="home-stream-meta home-stream-meta-reading">
          <a class="u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">
            <time class="dt-published" datetime="{{ post.published_at | htmlDateString }}">{{ post.published_at | dateDisplay }}</time>
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="home-stream-title-reading">
          <a class="p-name u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">{{ post.title }}</a>
        </p>
        {% if streamImage %}
          <a class="home-stream-media home-stream-media-reading u-url" href="{{ post | localPostUrl }}">
            <img class="home-stream-image home-stream-image-listening u-photo" src="{{ streamImage.src }}" alt="{{ streamImage.alt }}" loading="lazy">
          </a>
        {% endif %}
        <div class="home-stream-body home-stream-body-reading e-content">
          {% if post.excerpt %}
            <p>{{ post.excerpt }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="listening-note">
      See all reading posts <a href="/books/">here</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
  {% endif %}
</article>
